  "texts": [
    "Radiologists are more willing to accept false positives, if the model also identifies pathology that impresses the radiologist or would add value for the patient or other stakeholder.",
    "Disease prevalence also has a strong impact on downstream model acceptance.",
    "Low disease prevalence AI models produce results with numerous false positives limiting user acceptance.",
    "Disease prevalence in a patient group presented to an AI model can be modified by properly selecting patient imaging locations, such as Emergency Department, inpatient, or outpatient.",
    "Hence, some AI models may be deployed on a subset of exams because disease prevalence in that exam subset is increased from baseline."
  ],
